--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following is a list of the major customizations
made to the lua-5.1.4 sources for BZFlag.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Renamed Makefile to Makefile.orig, and  (svn r18913)
   src/Makefile to src/Makefile.org

2. Added Makefile.am  (svn r18913)

3. Made the following adjustments in luaconf.h:  (svn r18915)
     /* BZ#define LUA_NUMBER_DOUBLE */
     #undef LUA_NUMBER_DOUBLE

     /*BZ #define LUA_NUMBER  double */
     #define LUA_NUMBER  float

     /*BZ #define LUA_NUMBER_SCAN "%lf" */
     #define LUA_NUMBER_SCAN "%f"

4. Undefined (in luaconf.h):  (svn r18915)
       LUA_COMPAT_VARARG
       LUA_COMPAT_MOD
       LUA_COMPAT_LSTR
       LUA_COMPAT_GFIND
       LUA_COMPAT_OPENLIB

5. Applied the lua_pushhstring patch  (svn r18916)

6. Applied the LUA_CALLINSINDEX patch  (svn r18917)

7. Added lua_setuserdataextra() and lua_getuserdataextra() for
   faster userdata type checking  (svn r19238)

8. Renamed the source files from .c to .cxx for g++ compilation  (svn r19274)

9. Applied the __usedindex metamethod patch  (svn r19401)

10. Disabled precompiled chunks in luaU_undump()  (svn r19459)

11. Added the lpeg library

12. Added the table.readonly() feature

13. Added the table.create() feature

14. Added the lua_seterrorfunc() feature

15. Applied the mergesort patch

16. Applied the LUA_EZFOR_LOOP patch

17. Applied http://www.lua.org/ftp/patch-lua-5.1.4-3

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
